The paper proposes fast probabilistic algorithms with low communication volume to check the correctness of operations in Big Data processing frameworks and distributed databases. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.Distributed Systems. Among these, cs.DS and cs.DB are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the topic of Big Data processing and distributed databases. However, cs.DC, cs.CC, and cs.Distributed Systems are also possible categories, as they cover related topics such as distributed computing and communication efficiency.
